commit.message: macOS xfail seems to have fixed itself.
Add warning for overwritten init params.
Bug fix:Check params before maximizing parameter (#383)

Fix misleading error names

Raising error on `X <= 0` asserts that `X` is strictly positive.
Give up on the failing test for now.
Followup cleanup after drop of Py2 compat.

Move CI to azure; drop support for Py2.7.

Not worth fixing Azure Windows builds on Py2.7 / macOS builds on Py3.4.
Only validate Gaussian covars when setting them.
Warn instead of raise for degenerate GMMHMM covariances.
Shorten GMMHMM equations with shorter variable names.
Guard against negative probabilities arising from priors.
Warn if no transition from a state was ever observed.
